API¶

EPA SWMM Interface¶

class urbansurge.swmm_model.SWMM(config_path)¶
get_component_names(section)¶

Returns the names of all components for a given section. :param section: Section name. :return: List of component names.

get_link_depth()¶

Get link depth. :return: Pandas data frame of link depth.

get_link_flow()¶

Get link flow rate. :return: Pandas data frame of link flow rate.

get_link_geometry(link_id)¶

Gets a link’s geometry. :param link_id: Link ID. :return: Geometry of link. 4 item list for “Geom1” through “Geom4”

get_link_length(link_id)¶

Gets a link’s length. :param link_id: Link ID. :return: Length of link.

get_link_offsets(link_id)¶

Gets link upstream and downstream offsets. :param link_id: Link ID. :return: Link offsets as a tuple. (Inlet Offset, Outlet Offset)

get_link_roughness(link_id)¶

Gets a link’s roughness. :param link_id: Link ID. :return: Roughness of link.

get_link_seepage(link_id)¶

Gets link seepage rate. :param link_id: Link ID. :return: Link seepage rate.

get_link_velocity()¶

Get link velocity. :return: Pandas data frame of link velocity.

get_link_volume()¶

Get link volume. :return: Pandas data frame of link volume.

get_node_depth()¶

Get node depths. :return: Pandas data frame of node depths.

get_node_flooding()¶

Get node flooding. :return: Pandas data frame of node flooding.

get_node_head()¶

Get node head. :return: Pandas data frame of node head.

get_node_lateral_inflow()¶

Get node lateral inflow. :return: Pandas data frame of node lateral inflow.

get_node_ponded_volume()¶

Get node ponded volume. :return: Pandas data frame of node ponded volume.

get_node_total_inflow()¶

Get node total inflow. :return: Pandas data frame of node total inflow.

get_storage_outfall_link(storage_id)¶

Gets the outfall link for a storage component. :param storage_id: ID of storage unit. :return: ID of outfall link.

get_storage_property(storage_id, property)¶

Get the value of a storage property. :param storage_id: ID of storage unit. :param property: Name of the property. :return: Value of the storage property. Evaluates type automatically.

set_link_geometry(link_id, geom)¶

Set a link’s geometry. :param link_id: Link ID to edit. :param geom: Four item list with values for “Geom1” through “Geom4”. :return: Prints success if verbose.

set_link_length(link_id, length)¶

Set a link’s length. :param link_id: Link ID to edit. :param length: New link length. :return: Prints success if verbose.

set_link_offsets(link_id, offsets)¶

Sets the inlet and outlet offsets for a link. :param link_id: ID of the link. :param offsets: Link offsets as a tuple (Inlet Offset, Outlet Offset) :return: Offsets.

set_link_roughness(link_id, roughness)¶

Set a link’s roughness. :param link_id: Link ID to edit. :param roughness: New link roughness. :return: Prints success if verbose.

set_link_seepage(link_id, seepage_rate)¶

Set the link seepage rate. Roughly equivalent to hydraulic conductivity. :param link_id: ID of link. :param seepage_rate: Seepage rate in project units. :return: Prints success if verbose.

set_raingage_timeseries(raingage_id, timeseries_name)¶

Assign a timeseries to a rain gage. :param raingage_id: Rain gage ID. :param timeseries_name: Timeseries name. :return: None

set_storage_property(storage_id, property, property_value)¶

Get the value of a storage property. :param storage_id: ID of storage unit. :param property: Name of the property. :param property_value: New property value. :return: Prints success message.

unpack_series(series)¶

Unpacks SWMM output series into datetime and values.

urbansurge.file_utils.set_inp_section(in_filepath, section, column_name, component_name, new_value, out_filepath=None)¶
